---
description: MUI import and bundle hygiene for percona-ui — path imports, tooling, bundler notes.
globs: percona-ui/**/*.{ts,tsx}
alwaysApply: true
---

## Why

MUI ships size snapshots per commit; **barrel imports** (`@mui/material`, `@mui/icons-material`) hurt **dev startup/rebuild** most — not only bundle size. Prefer **default path imports** (matches MUI docs/examples).

## Imports

- **Components**: `import Button from '@mui/material/Button'` — not `import { Button } from '@mui/material'`.
- **Icons**: `import Delete from '@mui/icons-material/Delete'` — not `import { Delete } from '@mui/icons-material'` (icons: path imports much faster in dev).

## Migrate barrels → paths

```bash
npx @mui/codemod@latest v5.0.0/path-imports <path>
```

## ESLint (optional guard)

`no-restricted-imports` patterns: `{ "regex": "^@mui/[^/]+$" }` — blocks package root barrels only.

## VS Code auto-import

`.vscode/settings.json`: `typescript.preferences.autoImportSpecifierExcludeRegexes`: `["^@mui/[^/]+$"]` — nudges path imports.

## Bundlers

- **Next.js ≥13.5**: `optimizePackageImports` can optimize MUI imports; still prefer path imports for consistency unless team standard says otherwise.
- **Parcel**: set `"@parcel/resolver-default": { "packageExports": true }` in `package.json` so ESM/exports resolve correctly.
